{"word":"G3814 - παιδίσκη - paidískē - pahee-dis'-kay - Bondmaid","slug":"G3814","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">παιδίσκη</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>paidískē"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>pahee-dis'-kay"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bondmaid"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03B1;&#x03B9;&#x03B4;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C3;&#x03BA;&#x03B7; - paidiske&#x0304;</b> - <i>pahee-dis'-kay</i><p/>Feminine diminutive of <a href=\"#/G3816\">G3816</a>; a <i>girl</i>, that is, (specifically) a <i>female slave</i> or <i>servant:</i> - bondmaid (-woman), damsel, maid (-en)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3808\">G3808</a>, <a href=\"#/G3812\">G3812</a>, <a href=\"#/G3813\">G3813</a>, <a href=\"#/G3816\">G3816</a>"}]}